Package: THEfunc
Type: Package
Title: Tumor Heterogeneity and Evolution functions
Version: 0.0.9
Author: Andrew Lynch <arlynch1001@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Andrew Lynch <arlynch1001@gmail.com>
Description: Assorted functions for analyzing/visualizing genomic data with a focus twoard tumor heterogeneity and evolution. The package is roughly broken in 4 parts. 
    (1) Input - Functions for reading in genomic data from various sources.
    (2) Calculations - Functions to deal with quantities related to THE such as allele frequencies, cancer cell fraction, multiplicity, purity, and ploidy.
    (3) SeqPlot - A flexible suite of tools for visualizing genomic data.
    (4) Utilities - A smorgasbord of other useful functions.
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10),
    GenomicRanges(>= 1.30)
Imports:
    VariantAnnotation,
    StructuralVariantAnnotation,
    R6,
    grid,
    rtracklayer
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: https://github.com/andrewrlynch/THEfunc
BugReports: https://github.com/andrewrlynch/THEfunc/issues
